[2026-03-13T17:44:27Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01CDMiNsYDeokNGDGPoWKGXF","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a comprehensive understanding of the codebase. Let me compile my findings:\n\n## Summary of Web UI Workflow Graph Rendering Files\n\nI've completed a thorough search of the codebase for all files related to web UI workflow graph rendering. Here are my findings:\n\n### **HTML Templates** (Graph and UI Layout)\n\n1. **`/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html`** - Main workflow graph rendering template\n   - Contains the `showWorkflow()` function (lines 166-406) which is the core DAG rendering logic\n   - Implements sophisticated graph layout algorithm:\n     - Topological sort (Kahn's algorithm) for layer assignment\n     - Sugiyama-style longest-path layering\n     - Barycenter-based ordering to minimize edge crossings (4-pass algorithm)\n     - Bezier curve edge drawing with merge patterns for terminal nodes\n   - Generates SVG visualization with:\n     - Node rectangles with icons (emoji: 📄 script, 🤖 agent, 🔄 workflow)\n     - Curved edges with arrowheads\n     - Terminal nodes (done/abort) with special styling\n     - Merge collectors for multiple wires to same terminal\n     - Edge labels showing result conditions\n   - Contains workflow loading and tab switching logic (loadWorkflows, switchLocation, renderWorkflowTabs)\n   - Includes step detail drawer functionality (openDrawer, closeDrawer)\n\n2. **`/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/run_detail.html`** - Run execution detail page\n   - Displays step execution history and logs\n   - Real-time log streaming via SSE (Server-Sent Events)\n   - Step output accordion view\n   - Live polling for run state updates\n\n3. **`/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/projects.html`** - Project overview page\n   - Project cards with health indicators\n   - Recent run history visualization\n\n4. **`/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/runs.html`** - Runs list page\n   - Tabular view of all runs with filtering\n   - Project-based filtering\n   - Run timing and state display\n\n5. **`/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/layout.html`** - Base layout template\n   - Navigation bar and container structure\n   - Base template for all pages\n\n### **CSS Stylesheets** (Graph Styling)\n\n**`/workspace/internal/adapters/web/static/style.css`** - Complete styling for all UI elements including:\n- **DAG/Workflow Graph Styles** (lines 460-496):\n  - `.dag-svg` - SVG container styling\n  - `.dag-node-rect` - Step node rectangles with hover effects\n  - `.dag-node-text` - Step text labels\n  - `.dag-edge` - Connection lines between steps\n  - `.dag-edge-label` - Result condition labels on edges\n  - `.dag-terminal-done` / `.dag-terminal-abort` - Terminal node styling with special colors\n  - `.dag-merge-line` - Dashed lines for merge patterns\n  - `.dag-merge-dot` - Dots marking merge points\n- **Drawer Styles** (lines 498-555) - Slide-out panel for step details\n- **Various UI Components** - Tables, badges, buttons, panels, tabs, log viewer\n\n### **Go Handler Code** (Backend API and Graph Data)\n\n**`/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go`** - Web server and API handlers:\n\n- **Routes** (lines 146-165):\n  - `GET /api/projects/{name}/workflows` - Returns workflow graph data (line 161)\n  - `GET /api/projects/{name}/workflows/{workflow}/steps/{step}/content` - Step content delivery (line 162)\n  - Other runs, projects, and stream endpoints\n\n- **Workflow Graph Data API** (lines 1330-1437):\n  - `handleAPIWorkflows()` function - Parses and returns workflow graph structure\n  - Returns JSON with:\n    - Steps array with: name, type (agent/script/workflow), results, config\n    - Wires array with: from, result, to (connection definitions)\n    - EntryStep: starting step name\n    - Location: container or host\n  \n  - **Data structures**:\n    - `apiWire` struct (lines 1335-1339): From, Result, To\n    - `apiStepDef` struct (lines 1338-1343): Name, Type, Results, Config\n    - `apiWorkflow` struct (lines 1344-1351): Name, File, Location, Steps, Wires, EntryStep\n\n- **Container workflows**: Parses all `.cloche/*.cloche` files (except host.cloche)\n- **Host workflows**: Parses `.cloche/host.cloche` for host-side orchestration\n\n- **Web Page Handlers**:\n  - `handleProjectDetail()` - Serves project detail page with graph\n  - `handleRunDetail()` - Serves individual run execution page\n\n### **Domain Models** (Workflow Structure)\n\n**`/workspace/internal/domain/workflow.go`** - Core workflow data types:\n- `Workflow` struct - Contains Steps, Wiring, EntryStep\n- `Step` struct (lines 35-40) - Name, Type, Results, Config\n- `Wire` struct (lines 42-47) - From, Result, To, OutputMap\n- `StepType` enum - agent, script, workflow\n- Workflow validation and reachability analysis\n\n### **Test Files** (Validation)\n\n**`/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler_test.go`** - Tests for graph rendering:\n- Tests verify DAG rendering elements appear in HTML\n- Tests check for specific SVG classes: `workflow-dag`, `dag-merge-dot`\n\n### **Key Visualization Technologies**\n\n- **No external libraries** - Pure SVG generation with vanilla JavaScript\n- **Layout algorithm**: Hybrid approach combining:\n  - Topological sorting\n  - Sugiyama-style hierarchical layout\n  - Barycenter-based layer ordering\n  - Bezier curves for edge routing\n- **Responsive**: Dynamic positioning based on layer count and node distribution\n- **Interactive**: Click nodes to view step details in drawer panel\n- **Real-time**: SSE-based log streaming and polling for run state updates\n\n### File Structure Reference\n\n```\n/workspace/internal/adapters/web/\n├── handler.go                           # Web server & API handlers\n├── handler_test.go                      # Handler tests\n├── handler_stream_test.go               # Streaming tests\n├── templates/\n