ves project detail page with graph\n  - `handleRunDetail()` - Serves individual run execution page\n\n### **Domain Models** (Workflow Structure)\n\n**`/workspace/internal/domain/workflow.go`** - Core workflow data types:\n- `Workflow` struct - Contains Steps, Wiring, EntryStep\n- `Step` struct (lines 35-40) - Name, Type, Results, Config\n- `Wire` struct (lines 42-47) - From, Result, To, OutputMap\n- `StepType` enum - agent, script, workflow\n- Workflow validation and reachability analysis\n\n### **Test Files** (Validation)\n\n**`/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler_test.go`** - Tests for graph rendering:\n- Tests verify DAG rendering elements appear in HTML\n- Tests check for specific SVG classes: `workflow-dag`, `dag-merge-dot`\n\n### **Key Visualization Technologies**\n\n- **No external libraries** - Pure SVG generation with vanilla JavaScript\n- **Layout algorithm**: Hybrid approach combining:\n  - Topological sorting\n  - Sugiyama-style hierarchical layout\n  - Barycenter-based layer ordering\n  - Bezier curves for edge routing\n- **Responsive**: Dynamic positioning based on layer count and node distribution\n- **Interactive**: Click nodes to view step details in drawer panel\n- **Real-time**: SSE-based log streaming and polling for run state updates\n\n### File Structure Reference\n\n```\n/workspace/internal/adapters/web/\n├── handler.go                           # Web server & API handlers\n├── handler_test.go                      # Handler tests\n├── handler_stream_test.go               # Streaming tests\n├── templates/\n│   ├── layout.html                      # Base layout\n│   ├── projects.html                    # Projects listing\n│   ├── project_detail.html              # PROJECT GRAPH (main file)\n│   ├── runs.html                        # Runs listing\n│   └── run_detail.html                  # Run execution detail\n└── static/\n    └── style.css                        # All UI styles including DAG CSS\n```\n\nThe workflow graph visualization is p