[2026-03-13T17:45:05Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01PZEESpjDujaUhymjWbNvus","type":"tool_result","content":"   140→\n   141→### Display\n   142→- Two-level tab navigation:\n   143→  - **Location tabs** (Container / Host) shown when both container and host workflows exist\n   144→  - **Workflow tabs** shown when the active location has multiple workflows\n   145→- Per workflow: a read-only DAG rendered client-side\n   146→  - Nodes = steps, rendered as boxes showing step name + type icon (agent 🤖 / script 📜 / workflow 🔁)\n   147→  - Edges = wires, labeled with the result name (e.g. `success`, `fail`)\n   148→  - Terminal nodes `done` and `abort` rendered distinctly\n   149→- Clicking a step node opens a right-side **drawer panel** (CSS slide-in):\n   150→  - Step name and type\n   151→  - Results list\n   152→  - `max_attempts` if set\n   153→  - For agent steps: full content of the referenced prompt file (loaded on demand)\n   154→  - For script steps: the `command`/`script` string or contents of the referenced script file\n   155→  - For host script steps: contents of a referenced script file under `.cloche/scripts/` (text files only); the content panel is hidden when no displayable content is available\n   156→  - For workflow steps: displays the dispatched workflow name\n   157→  - Drawer closes via X button or Escape, returning focus to the DAG without page reload\n   158→\n   159→### DAG rendering\n   160→Client-side Sugiyama-style layered layout with no external library. Steps are assigned to\n   161→layers via longest-path from sources, then ordered within each layer using barycenter\n   162→heuristic (4 forward/backward passes) to minimize edge crossings. Layout flows\n   163→left-to-right with SVG Bezier curve edges.\n   164→\n   165→When multiple wires target the same terminal (`done` or `abort`), they merge into a\n   166→collector bus: individual curves from each source converge on a vertical dashed line,\n   167→which feeds a single arrow into the terminal node. This reduces wire clutter as graphs\n   168→grow in complexity.\n   169→\n   170→The DAG container scrolls horizontally when the graph exceeds the panel width.\n   171→\n   172→### API additions\n   173→\n   174→```\n   175→GET /api/projects/{name}/workflows\n   176→```\n   177→\n   178→Response:\n   179→```json\n   180→[\n   181→  {\n   182→    \"name\": \"develop\",\n   183→    \"file\": \".cloche/develop.cloche\",\n   184→    \"location\": \"container\",\n   185→    \"steps\": [\n   186→      {\n   187→        \"name\": \"implement\",\n   188→        \"type\": \"agent\",\n   189→        \"results\": [\"success\", \"fail\"],"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9677d0b8-19e6-412e-8355-79a7a9e3015b","uuid":"c2bf6a90-e294-480e-a98c-3f2db2a5d11e","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-project-pages-design.md","content":"\n### Display\n- Two-level tab navigation:\n  - **Location tabs** (Container / Host) shown when both container and host workflows exist\n  - **Workflow tabs** shown when the active location has multiple workflows\n- Per workflow: a read-only DAG rendered client-side\n  - Nodes = steps, rendered as boxes showing step name + type icon (agent 🤖 / script 📜 / workflow 🔁)\n  - Edges = wires, labeled with the result name (e.g. `success`, `fail`)\n  - Terminal nodes `done` and `abort` rendered distinctly\n- Clicking a step node opens a right-side **drawer panel** (CSS slide-in):\n  - Step name and type\n  - Results list\n  - `max_attempts` if set\n  - For agent steps: full content of the referenced prompt file (loaded on demand)\n  - For script steps: the `command`/`script` string or contents of the referenced script file\n  - For host script steps: contents of a referenced script file under `.cloche/scripts/` (text files only); the content panel is hidden when no displayable content is available\n  - For workflow steps: displays the dispatched workflow name\n  - Drawer closes via X button or Escape, returning focus to the DAG without page reload\n\n### DAG rendering\nClient-side Sugiyama-style layered layout with no external library. Steps are assigned to\nlayers via longest-path from sources, then ordered within each layer using barycenter\nheuristic (4 forward/backward passes) to minimize edge crossings. Layout flows\nleft-to-right with SVG Bezier curve edges.\n\nWhen multiple wires target the same terminal (`done` or `abort`), they merge into a\ncollector bus: individual curves from each source converge on a vertical dashed line,\nwhich feeds a single arrow into the terminal node. This reduces wire clutter as graphs\ngrow in complexity.\n\nThe DAG container scrolls horizontally when the graph exceeds the panel width.\n\n### API additions\n\n```\nGET /api/projects/{name}/workflows\n```\n\nResponse:\n```json\n[\n  {\n    \"name\": \"develop\",\n    \"file\": \".cloche/develop.cloche\",\n    \"location\": \"container\",\n    \"steps\": [\n      {\n        \"name\": \"implement\",\n        \"type\": \"agent\",\n        \"results\": [\"success\", \"fail\"],","numLines":50,"startLine":140,"totalLines":228}}}
